originalText.text: Parked there for 3 hours and this is what happened to our car. If you have to park there(I would choose street parking than parking in this garage), please take pictures of your car before and after so you have prove if anything happens to your car. This could cost us couple hundred dollars to fix it… so frustrating…

originalText.text: Never park here and I had a horrible experience since parking staff closed the garage before 11pm and they forced me to pay 3 days charge (without receipt) for less than 24 hours parking for their mistake and had to spend another $300 dollars for my commute purpose from New York to New Jersey (Taxi & Bus) and struggled a lot with my 2 kids due to their mistake. This is a big scam to earn more money and they purposefully close the garage 15-20 mins before the actual closing time (11pm) and they cheat you with some manual punching machine as an evidence. I was asking to share his boss contact details and parking staff refused to share. I would suggest you to go for 24 hours parking garage since they never close their garage though it might be $10 or $20 more, otherwise you would end up spending ~$300 dollars.

originalText.text: Como recomendación no parqueen en este lugar, el trabajador de nombre JHON , logró estafarnos luego de indicarnos que debíamos pagar un precio muy diferente al que nos cobraron. evidentemente este señor, por captar clientes ofrece tarifas  que al momento de recoger el vehículo son totalmente falsas y sin autorización de la administración.

text.text: As a recommendation, do not park in this place, the worker named JHON managed to scam us after telling us that we had to pay a very different price than the one they charged us. Obviously this man, in order to attract clients, offers rates that at the time of picking up the vehicle are totally false and without authorization from the administration.
